videos.headline: Cummins to Sai Sudharsan, out Caught by Abhishek Sharma!! Gone! Is there still life left in this contest? 119.8kph, slower ball into the wicket, Sai Sudharsan spots it and goes after it with a pull shot. Connects well but hits it flat to deep midwicket. Abhishek holds onto the catch and the 64-run stand has been broken. Sai Sudharsan c Abhishek Sharma b Cummins 45(36) [4s-4 6s-1]

Markande to Shubman Gill, out Caught by Abdul Samad!! A wicket immediately after the timeout and it's the set batter! 84.6kph, tossed up, scrambled seam, full around leg and probably off the front of the hand. The GT captain shimmies down the track in an attempt to loft it over wide long-on. Gets too close to the pitch of the ball and gets it off the bottom part of the bat. Samad moves to his right from long-on to take a safe catch. Much-needed wicket for SRH! Shubman Gill c Abdul Samad b Markande 36(28) [4s-2 6s-1]

Shahbaz Ahmed to Saha, out Caught by Cummins!! Catching practice at mid-on - On a length and angling into the right-hander, Saha was looking to carve it over the on-side, but he doesn't get a lot of power behind the shot, chips it in the air and Cummins completes the catch, running back at mid-on. Saha c Cummins b Shahbaz Ahmed 25(13) [4s-1 6s-2]

Mohit Sharma to Cummins, out Abdul Samad Run Out!! 1 run completed. A run-out to end the innings - Samad was looking for a second, Cummins said yes and then sent him back. Saha fumbles slightly, but he has plenty of time to break the stumps, finding Samad well short. Was a slower short ball and Samad pulled it to deep backward square leg. Abdul Samad run out (Noor Ahmad/Saha) 29(14) [4s-3 6s-1]

Mohit Sharma to Washington Sundar, out Caught by Rashid Khan!! .. And he lasts exaactly one ball, but he has a bigger job with the ball. Was another slower short ball from Mohit, bowled into the surface and gave Sundar no pace to work it - he rocked back on the pull, hit it flat and hard, straight down Rashid's throat at deep mid-wicket. Mohit finds himself on a hat-trick. Washington Sundar c Rashid Khan b Mohit Sharma 0(1)

Mohit Sharma to Shahbaz Ahmed, out Caught by Rahul Tewatia!!Catching practice at long-on - the slower ones doing the trick for Mohit in the death overs once again. Was full and just outside off, bowled from the back-of-the hand - Shahbaz was early into the lofted drive, came off the toe-end and lobbed to long-on. Shahbaz Ahmed c Rahul Tewatia b Mohit Sharma 22(20) [4s-1 6s-1]

Umesh Yadav to Markram, out Caught by Rashid Khan!! A gentle chip and Markram has holed out to long-on - he looks at his bat as he walks away, wasn't intented to go that far, but the timing is sublime and Rashid grabs the ball on the slide. SRH are in some trouble now - length ball at the stujmps - Markram didn't go full tilt on the on-drive, was merely looking to chip it down the ground, Rashid runs in, it came at an awkward height, but he manages to reverse cup in style. Markram c Rashid Khan b Umesh Yadav 17(19)

Umesh Yadav to Markram, out Caught by Rashid Khan!! A gentle chip and Markram has holed out to long-on - he looks at his bat as he walks away, wasn't intented to go that far, but the timing is sublime and Rashid grabs the ball on the slide. SRH are in some trouble now - length ball at the stujmps - Markram didn't go full tilt on the on-drive, was merely looking to chip it down the ground, Rashid runs in, it came at an awkward height, but he manages to reverse cup in style. Markram c Rashid Khan b Umesh Yadav 17(19)

Rashid Khan to Klaasen, out Bowled!! That's a massive wicket and Rashid has his arms up in delight - Klaasen smashes his bat with his hands as he walks away fuming, was the wrong 'un and it was sportted by Klaasen. But the ball skid on and went straight, Klaasen was backing away, looking to pull it with the turn, he misses and the ball crashes into the leg-stump. He was starting to look dangerous, but SRH have lost their 4th wicket now. Klaasen b Rashid Khan 24(13) [4s-1 6s-2]

Mohit Sharma to Abhishek Sharma, out Caught by Shubman Gill!! The slower ball has done the trick! Another key wicket for GT. 124.9kph back of a length ball on off, Abhishek Sharma is through his punch early and ends up slicing it towards extra cover. His bottom hand also came off while playing that shot. Gill stationed there accepts the dolly. Abhishek Sharma c Shubman Gill b Mohit Sharma 29(20) [4s-2 6s-2]

Noor Ahmad to Head, out Bowled!! Knocked him over! Noor Ahmad is absolutely pumped up and why not! He has got the big fish. He bowls this one slow through the air outside off and it's the wrong 'un, Head actually picks it as he goes for the slog sweep but there's a big bat-pad gap. The ball goes right through that and crashes into the middle-stump. Smart bowling from the chinaman. Head b Noor Ahmad 19(14) [4s-3]

Azmatullah to Mayank, out Caught by Darshan Nalkande!! The move to give Azmatullah three overs on the trot has worked! A back of a length ball angling towards the leg-stump, Mayank is caught in the crease and is cramped for space. He goes for the swivel pull but doesn't get enough on it as the ball flies towards deep backward square leg. Nalkande stationed ther makes no mistake. Mayank has struggled against the short ball this season and that proves to be his downfall once again today. Mayank c Darshan Nalkande b Azmatullah 16(17) [4s-2]
